<td class="px-4 py-2 text-sm text-gray-700 border-b">gemini-1.5-pro, gemini-1.5-flash, gemini-2.0-flash</td>
<td class="px-4 py-2 text-sm text-gray-700 border-b">Vision, long context (1M-2M tokens)</td>
</tr>
<tr class="hover:bg-gray-50">
<td class="px-4 py-2 text-sm text-gray-700 border-b"><strong>Mistral</strong></td>
<td class="px-4 py-2 text-sm text-gray-700 border-b">mistral-large, mistral-small, mixtral-8x7b</td>
<td class="px-4 py-2 text-sm text-gray-700 border-b">European alternative, function calling</td>
</tr>
<tr class="hover:bg-gray-50">
<td class="px-4 py-2 text-sm text-gray-700 border-b"><strong>Groq</strong></td>
<td class="px-4 py-2 text-sm text-gray-700 border-b">llama-3.1-70b, llama-3.1-8b, mixtral</td>
<td class="px-4 py-2 text-sm text-gray-700 border-b">Speed via Groq LPU</td>
</tr>
<tr class="hover:bg-gray-50">
<td class="px-4 py-2 text-sm text-gray-700 border-b"><strong>Hugging Face</strong></td>
<td class="px-4 py-2 text-sm text-gray-700 border-b">Any inference endpoint</td>
<td class="px-4 py-2 text-sm text-gray-700 border-b">Custom / open-source models</td>
</tr>
<tr class="hover:bg-gray-50">
<td class="px-4 py-2 text-sm text-gray-700 border-b"><strong>Workers AI</strong></td>
<td class="px-4 py-2 text-sm text-gray-700 border-b">llama, qwen, deepseek-r1-distill</td>
<td class="px-4 py-2 text-sm text-gray-700 border-b">Free inference on Cloudflare's edge</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table></div>
<p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4">
The Workers AI models are a special case: when you route to a Workers AI model through the gateway, the inference runs on Cloudflare's network and the model itself is free (you only pay Workers request + CPU fees). This is useful for cost-sensitive batch workloads on smaller models (Llama 3.1 8B, Qwen 1.5B, DeepSeek R1 Distill). 
</p>
<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">How It Compares To Portkey, LiteLLM, And OpenRouter</h2>
<div class="overflow-x-auto my-6"><table class="min-w-full divide-y divide-gray-200 border border-gray-200">
